# Setup #

```
npm install -g yarn
npm install -g ts-node
npm install -g typescript@2.x.x
yarn install
```

# Usage #

```
npm run (cmd)
```

* `cmd` is a command from the lists below

```
ts-node run --host=(host) --https=(https) --http=(http)
```

* `host` is the host to bind
* `https` is the https port to bind
* `http` is the http port to bind

# Commands #

##### Tools #####

* `ts-node` : ts-node
* `http-server` : http-server
* `typedoc` : typedoc
* `tslint` : tslint
* `mocha` : mocha
* `nyc` : nyc

##### Clean #####

* `clean` : __alias__ for `clean:all`
* `clean:all` : __alias__ for `clean:analyze`, `clean:coverage`, `clean:dist`, `clean:modules`, `clean:doc`
* `clean:analyze` : clean `/doc/analyze` using rm -rf
* `clean:coverage` : clean `/doc/coverage` using rm -rf
* `clean:dist` : clean `/dist` using rm -rf
* `clean:modules` : clean `/node_modules` using rm -rf
* `clean:doc` : clean `/doc/typedoc` using rm -rf

##### Serve #####

* `start` : __alias__ for `serve`
* `serve` : serve `/src` using ts-node
    * See : [http://localhost:3080](http://localhost:3080)
* `serve:log` : __alias__ for `serve` with logs
* `serve:log:bak` : __alias__ for `serve` with logs in background
* `serve:analyze` : serve `/doc/analyze` using http-server
    * See : [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)
* `serve:coverage` : serve `/doc/coverage` using http-server
    * See : [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)
* `serve:dist` : serve `/dist` using http-server
    * See : [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)
* `serve:doc` : serve `/doc/typedoc` using http-server
    * See : [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)

##### Documentation #####

* `doc` : run `documentation generation` to `/doc/typedoc` using typedoc

##### Static Code Analysis #####

* `lint` : run `static analysis` to `/doc/analyze` using tslint

##### Unit Tests #####

* `test` : __alias__ for `test:all`
* `test:one -- (test)` : run one `unit test` using mocha
* `test:all` : run all `unit tests` using mocha

##### Package #####

* `version` : __alias__ for `test`

# Notes #

* See : `package.json`
